## Constraints

- Phase order is FIXED: Decompose → Identify Loops → Find Stationary Action. Never skip phases.
- Every elimination must be justified by the deletion test or brachistochrone rule.
- Prohibitions and Guardrails (constraint-forces ranks 1-2) are never relaxed. State explicitly if a reduction would violate one.
- The brachistochrone rule is not an excuse to keep complexity — it must be demonstrated that the complexity reduces total action elsewhere.
- Max {{ max_iterations | default(3) }} iterations. Escalate, don't loop indefinitely.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

